"Undocumented immigrants" and "illegal aliens" are often used interchangeably to refer to the same group of people. Both terms have their own nuances, but they essentially mean the same thing: individuals who are present in a country without proper authorization.The term "undocumented" emphasizes the lack of legal documentation, while "illegal alien" highlights the violation of immigration laws. Some people prefer one term over the other based on their perspective or political stance.Regardless of which term is used, it is important to remember that these individuals are human beings and deserve respect and dignity, regardless of their immigration status.
